{"word":"τητάομαι","slug":"τητάομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>τητάομαι</b></el> <el>(τητάομαι,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>τήτη</el>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only used in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <i>to be in want, suffer want</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>; <el>τὸ τητᾶσθαι</el> <i>privation</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>to be in want of, be deprived</i> or <i>bereft of</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}